  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The upcoming scholarly work *Pro-vax*, published by Peter Lang Verlag in 2025, showcases a significant commitment to sustainability and policy relevance, evidenced by its alignment with Sustainable Development Goals (SDG) and a notable scholarly uptake reflected by its initial citations.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">*Pro-vax*, a forthcoming scholarly publication by Peter Lang Verlag, aims to address pressing issues surrounding vaccination through an academic lens. This work is particularly relevant within the domain of sustainability and policy, demonstrated by its association with at least one Sustainable Development Goal. Such alignment suggests that the authors are not only contributing to academic discourse but also addressing wider societal challenges.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While there is currently no available data indicating online mentions or community discourse surrounding this work, its scholarly uptake is beginning to show promise, with one citation already noted. This early indication of engagement suggests that *Pro-vax* is poised to influence ongoing discussions in the field. Scholarly uptake is often a precursor to broader discussions, and as such, this initial citation may signify incoming interest from researchers and policy-makers alike.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of substantial metadata in terms of community engagement or mentions thus far does not detract from the work\u2019s potential impact. Academic works often take time to gain traction in public and online forums, especially when addressing complex issues such as vaccination. As the discourse evolves, there is an opportunity for *Pro-vax* to contribute to public understanding and policy-making through its rigorous analysis and findings.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In conclusion, *Pro-vax* represents a significant scholarly effort within its field, focusing on sustainability and policy relevance. With its early signals of academic interest, this work may transform into an influential resource as it becomes fully available to the research community and beyond, encouraging further academic and public engagement over time.</p>",
